data.database_description: The database is designed to manage and track interactions between individuals and organizations with various services, forms, addresses, and parties involved in transactions or communications. It captures detailed information about service offerings, form processing, individual and organizational contact details, and address management for different parties. The schema facilitates tracking the lifecycle of forms and services, recording the relationships between entities through foreign keys that link tables like Individuals to Organizations via contacts, Parties to Addresses, Forms, and Services. Overall, this database supports a robust system for managing service bookings, form completions, organizational communications, and address records within a structured relational framework.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each address record.
Street number and building name or number.
Name of the town or city where the address is located.
Postal code for the address location.
State, province, or county name associated with the address.
Country where the address is located.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores detailed physical address information for various entities.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each service entry.
Categorizes the service (e.g., Education, Health).
The name of the service offered.
Detailed description of what the service entails.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Contains details about different services offered, categorized by type.

columns.columnDescription: Serves as the primary key for identifying a unique form.
Categorizes the form as either Basic or Complex.
Foreign key linking to the Services table, indicating which service the form is associated with.
Unique number assigned to each form for identification purposes.
The name of the form (e.g., SSN Application).
Detailed description explaining the purpose or contents of the form.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about various forms, their types, and associated services.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each individual.
First name of the individual.
Middle name of the individual, if any.
Contact phone number for the individual.
Email address of the individual.
Physical address of the individual.
Last name of the individual.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each organization.
Date and time when the organization was formed.
Name of the organization.
VAT number of the organization in the UK.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Contains details about organizations including formation dates and identification numbers.

columns.columnDescription: Serves as the primary key for identifying a unique party.
Specifies the preferred payment method of the party (e.g., Cheque, Credit Card, Cash).
Phone number associated with the party.
Email address associated with the party.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about individuals or entities interacting with services, including their contact and payment method details.

columns.columnDescription: Identifier linking to an individual in the Individuals table.
Identifier linking to an organization in the Organizations table.
Start date and time of the contact period.
End date and time of the contact period.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Tracks interactions between individuals and organizations over specific time periods.

columns.columnDescription: Identifier for the party associated with an address.
Identifier for the address linked to a party.
Start date and time when the address became valid for the party.
Type of address usage (e.g., Residence, Billing).
End date and time when the address ceased to be valid for the party.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Links addresses to parties and tracks the validity period of each association.

columns.columnDescription: Identifies the party involved in the form interaction.
Specifies the unique identifier of the form being processed.
Records the date and time when the completion of the form was initiated.
Describes the current status of the form processing (e.g., Completed, Partially Completed, Not Started).
Records the date and time when the form was fully completed.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Tracks interactions between parties and forms, including form processing status and completion dates.

columns.columnDescription: A unique identifier for each booking.
Identifier linking to a specific party who has booked the service (foreign key reference to Parties.party_id).
Identifier of the service being booked (foreign key reference to Services.service_id).
Scheduled date and time when the service is to be performed.
Date and time when the booking was made.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Tracks service bookings made by parties, including details of when the booking was made and when the service is scheduled.
